External Tool Setup for OCR Processing & Local-to-Cloud Connectivity

This task requires three external tools:

Poppler → Converts PDF pages into images
Tesseract OCR → Extracts text from images
Ngrok → Exposes local services to the internet for Boomi cloud access

Because apparently enterprise automation still needs a scavenger hunt of utilities just to read a document. Remarkable species, humans.

1. Poppler Setup
What is Poppler?

Poppler is used to convert PDF pages into images before OCR processing.

Since Tesseract performs OCR primarily on images, Poppler acts as the preprocessing layer.

📌 Install Poppler (Windows)
Step 1: Download Poppler

Download Poppler for Windows from:
https://github.com/oschwartz10612/poppler-windows/releases

Poppler for Windows Download

Step 2: Extract Poppler Files

Extract the downloaded ZIP file.

Example extracted folder:

C:\poppler-24.08.0

Inside the folder:

Library
 └── bin

Example full path:

C:\poppler-24.08.0\Library\bin
Step 3: Add Poppler to System PATH

Open:

Environment Variables

Navigate to:

System Variables → Path

Click:

Edit → New
Add:
C:\poppler-24.08.0\Library\bin
Save changes
✅ Verify Installation

Open Command Prompt and run:

pdftoppm -h

If installation is successful, Poppler version details will appear.

▶️ Convert PDF to Images

Example command:

pdftoppm input.pdf output -png
Command Explanation
Parameter	Description
input.pdf	Source PDF file
output	Output image prefix
-png	Converts pages into PNG images

Generated output:

output-1.png
output-2.png
output-3.png

Each PDF page becomes a separate image.

2. Tesseract OCR Setup
What is Tesseract OCR?

Tesseract extracts text from images generated by Poppler.

Processing Flow:

PDF → Poppler → Image Files → Tesseract OCR → Extracted Text

An elegant pipeline assembled from open-source tools and mild desperation.

📌 Install Tesseract OCR (Windows)
Step 1: Download Installer

Download Tesseract from:
https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki

Tesseract OCR Windows Installer

Step 2: Install Tesseract

Install using default location:

C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR
Step 3: Add Tesseract to PATH

Add the following path in Environment Variables:

C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR
✅ Verify Installation

Run:

tesseract --version

If successful, version information will appear.

▶️ Run OCR on Images

Example:

tesseract output-1.png result -l eng
Command Explanation
Parameter	Description
output-1.png	Input image
result	Output text filename
-l eng	English language OCR

Generated file:

result.txt
▶️ OCR Directly from PDF (Optional)
tesseract input.pdf output -l eng

However, converting PDF pages to images using Poppler generally provides better OCR accuracy.

Because PDFs enjoy hiding text layers in ways only software architects understand.

3. Ngrok Setup
What is Ngrok?

Ngrok exposes local applications to the internet through a secure public URL.

This allows:

Boomi Cloud → Local OCR Service

Without Ngrok, localhost remains trapped inside your machine like a tiny isolated kingdom.

📌 Install Ngrok (Windows)
Step 1: Download Ngrok

Download from:
https://ngrok.com/download/windows?tab=download
Ngrok Download

Step 2: Extract Files

Extract ZIP contents.

Example folder:

C:\ngrok
Step 3: Create Ngrok Account

Register account from:

Ngrok Dashboard Signup

Step 4: Copy Authentication Token

After login:

Open Dashboard
Copy the Auth Token

Example:

2aBcD123EXAMPLE_TOKEN
🔑 Configure Ngrok

Run the following command:

ngrok config add-authtoken <YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN>

Example:

ngrok config add-authtoken 2aBcD123EXAMPLE_TOKEN
✅ Verify Installation

Run:

ngrok version
▶️ Expose Local OCR Service

If your local OCR API/service runs on port:

9090

Run:

ngrok http 9090

Ngrok generates a public URL like:

https://abcd1234.ngrok-free.app
📌 Use in Boomi

Use the generated Ngrok URL as the:

Base URL

inside:

HTTP Client / API Connector

This enables Boomi cloud processes to connect with local OCR services.

🔄 Complete OCR Workflow
PDF File
   ↓
Poppler
(Convert PDF pages to images)
   ↓
Tesseract OCR
(Extract text from images)
   ↓
Local OCR API / Service
   ↓
Ngrok Public URL
   ↓
Boomi Cloud Process